<tr><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_04.gif"><img src="/lotr/gfx/mom/clear.gif" height=35 width=1></td>
<td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_05.gif" class="headerbg"><font class="h1font"><font color="#FFFFFF"><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 border=0 width=100%><TR><td><font class="h1font">Articles</td><form method='post' action=''><input type="hidden" name="PHPSESSID" value="586a5beb90d9908dc5528f9d0e11817c" /><td align='right' valign='bottom'><select name='select' onChange='go(this)'><option selected>More DeckTech Articles</option><option value='#'> </option><option value='/starwarsccg/articles/index.php3'>Star Wars: CCG</option><option value='/vs/articles/index.php'>Marvel VS</option><option value='/heroclix/articles/articles.php'>HeroClix</option><option value='/lotr/articles/articles.php'>Lord of the Rings</option><option value='/magic/articles/articles.php'>Video Games and Movies</option><option value='/wars/articles/articles.php'>Wizards Minis</option></select></td></form></tr></table></font></B></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_06.gif"></td></tr>
	<tr><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_07.gif"></td>
		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> -The Hearts of Men are easily corrupted-<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(4.39)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=15286'>David "Wyvern" Cauwenbergh</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=15286&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> August 8, 2004</font><p align='justify'><font class="bfont"> Boromir’s always been one of my favorite characters and I believe I can say that I was extremely pleased when Reflections came out, finally giving us the opportunity to play him as a ring-bearer.  <br />
<br />
The first time I saw his game text I thought, wow, this guy really is huge… allowing you to get rid of every minion he’s skirmishing provided he wins the skirmish…  <br />
Ever thought about finishing Shelob off with a single blow?  Boromir’s your guy…<br />
But then again, there’s his drawback…  if you want him to skirmish, you’ll either have to add 2 wounds or 3 burdens.  Even though you can modify this a bit by putting on the One Ring, I’d still have to say “Auch”…<br />
<br />
Ever since he came out, I’ve been thinking about a way to make him playable as a ring-bearer and here’s what I came up with…  Enjoy!<br />
<br />
Free peoples<br />
<br />
Starting<br />
Boromir, BOC<br />
The One Ring, ATAR<br />
Legolas, Greenleaf<br />
Arwen, either FEM or QoEaM<br />
<br />
Companions<br />
Aragorn, ET x4<br />
Sam, SoH<br />
Glorfindel, RiW<br />
Gil-Galad, EHK<br />
<br />
Possessions<br />
Aragorn’s bow x2<br />
Blade of Gondor x1<br />
Gwemegil x2<br />
Asfaloth x1<br />
Phial of Galadriel x2<br />
Elven Bow x1<br />
<br />
Conditions<br />
The Last Alliance of Elves and Men x2<br />
Gondor Bowmen x4<br />
Shadow Between x2<br />
<br />
Events<br />
Double Shot x2<br />
Company of Archers x2<br />
<br />
Allies<br />
Elrond, HtGG x2<br />
Galadriel, LotGW x1<br />
<br />
<br />
1. Deck type<br />
First thing I thought about was the sort of deck I would put Boromir in.  Would I opt for a Noble leaders deck, using Aragorn, Denethor and Faramir to get some damage bonuses or would I choose a Last Alliance deck?<br />
Eventually, I decided to opt for the latter.  <br />
Because of their versatility, I’ve always been a big fan of Last Alliance decks.  Weaken up your opponents’ minions with archery fire first, then slaughter what’s left of it with your high-strength companions.  These decks also benefit from condition removal and healing – and healing will become extremely important here…<br />
<br />
2. Companions<br />
When building a deck, one of the first things to decide is which companions to use.  The free peoples side, as shown above, contains 7 companions.  Try to make sure only five of these are on the tabel at a given time (who doesn’t fear an Enquea without proper protection?).  Ideally, you’ll have the following companions in play:<br />
Boromir – your ring-bearer, what more can I say?<br />
<br />
Aragorn, ET – your other Gondor Companion (see ‘Healing’ below as well).  Just like Boromir, you can exert him to use Gondor Bowman during the archery phase.  He also benefits from the Last Alliance of Elves and Men and can use his bow to get rid of minions.  <br />
<br />
Arwen, QoEaM – Give her Asfaloth and her blade and she’s a real mean fighting machine..  Arwen, FEM will do fine as well…<br />
<br />
Gil-Galad, EHK – He’ll solve your problems should any minions survive during the regroup phase, clearing the way for a double move…<br />
<br />
There’s two more companions in the deck – these serve mainly as a back-up.  There’s Sam, who can help you get rid of burdens - it would be a good idea to get rid of him as well afterwards :) and there’s Glorfindel, in case you’re in need of an extra fighter or if one of your companions managed to get himself killed.<br />
<br />
3. Burdens and Burden Removal<br />
The hearts of men are easily corrupted… and that certainly is true for Boromir.  A resistance of 6 isn’t really high – so we need to find a way to raise this a bit.  The scroll of Isildur would have been a good idea in a noble leaders deck, but since I won’t be using any artifacts in this deck, we’ll go for the phial of Galadriel instead – it’s in there twice – just to increase your chance of drawing it.<br />
Finally I’ve added Sam, SoH to the deck, in my opinion still the best way to get rid of burdens.  <br />
<br />
4. Healing and the Ring<br />
What we’re trying to do here is to make sure Boromir is able to skirmish as much as possible – assisting your other companions on the road to site 9.  Since we don’t want to overburden Boromir, we’re going to add wounds instead.  In order to give Boromir some more Vitality, I’ve decided to chose ATAR as the Ring.<br />
  <br />
Because your companions will be exerting a lot, or - in Boromir’s case – will be taking a lot of wounds, we’ll need to set up a decent healing machine.  <br />
There are two allies in the Deck – Elrond, who allows you to heal a companion during the regroup phase and Galadriel who’s there to make sure your elves stay healthy enough.<br />
By using Aragorn, ET we can transfer wounds from the ring-bearer to the elves.  The elves can be healed afterwards with Shadow Between.  <br />
<br />
Multiple copies of Aragorn and Gil-Galad will also help with the healing.<br />
<br />
5. Archery and Condition removal<br />
What’s an archery deck without Gondor Bowmen?  This card is so good it just has to be in there – 4 times…Double shot is also quite decent – since it requires an Elven archer to play, I’ve decided to include an extra bow for Gil-Galad.  You never know when your opponent decides to ‘hate’ your Legolas…<br />
Legolas and Gorn (with his bow) can provide you with direct archery – which is always handy of course.<br />
<br />
Company of archers will help you get rid of conditions.  I could have chosen ‘secret sentinels instead’ but realised the deck might need an extra ally for that (there’s only 3 in there).  <br />
<br />
6. The Blade and the Last Alliance<br />
The fact that it’s not unique makes ‘The Last Alliance’ extremely suited for this deck.  It can be played on Boromir as well as on Aragorn.  Since you’ll be spotting three elves most of the time, you’ll get the maximum strength bonus.  <br />
<br />
The Blade of Gondor finally is very nice against swarm decks.  In combination with a Last Alliance, Boromir will be strength 12 (strength 14 when wearing the ring), which should be enough to get rid of most minions.<br />
<br />
Here you go, guess that’s it for now.   Thanks for reading and I hope you enjoyed it :)<br />
<br />
Cheers from Belgium!  <br />
